    <note>Chen(1) Guoting [8003] His original mingzi was Yangting. Liangzhe TZ, 124.12a; Liangzhe jinshi zhi, 10.22a. He was an executive censor during Huizong's reign and impeached Wang(2) Fu [8146], Cai(1) Jing [1649] and Zhu Mian (not in dataset) and was purged (exiled to Huangzhou). When Qinzong succeeded to the throne he was made a member of the State council and was captured by Jin and died in exile in Beijing. CBD, 3, 2631.</note>
